OL,3,CFans emotional as Scotland kicks off
OL,4,Cfirst World Cup game in 28 years
OL,6,FFootball fans have shared their
OL,7,Femotion as the Flower of Scotland was
OL,8,Fheard on the World Cup stage for the
OL,9,Ffirst time in 28 years.
OL,11,FScotland kicked off their match
OL,12,Fagainst Haiti at the Boston Stadium on
OL,13,FSaturday at 9pm local time - 2am
OL,14,FSunday morning BST.
OL,16,FIt is the first time the side has
OL,17,Fqualified for the men's World Cup
OL,18,Fsince 1998, with thousands of
OL,19,Fdedicated fans expected to travel to
OL,20,Fthe US to watch the games.
