OL,3,CFans emotional as Scotland kicks off
OL,4,Cfirst World Cup game in 28 years
OL,6,FFootage from the OVO Hydro, in
OL,7,FGlasgow, showed thousands of people
OL,8,Fbelting out the anthem as they watched
OL,9,Fthe match on the big screen.
OL,11,FAn estimated 40,000 Scotland fans have
OL,12,Fmade the trip to the US to watch the
OL,13,Fgames, with First Minister John
OL,14,FSwinney among them.
OL,16,FSpeaking ahead of the game at The
OL,17,FHaven, a Scottish pub in Boston,
OL,18,FSwinney said: "The atmosphere is
OL,19,Felectric here in Boston, it has been
OL,20,Fsince we arrived.
